then calculates and returns the total length of the remaining names.To find \
the largest triangle that can be inscribed in a semicircle, we can utilize \
the properties of geometry. The largest triangle that can be inscribed in a \
semicircle is a right triangle whose base lies along the diameter of the \
semicircle.\n\nHere\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a Python function that calculates the \
area of the largest triangle that can be inscribed in a semicircle with a \
given radius:\n\n```python\nimport math\n\ndef largest_triangle_area(radius):\
\n    # The largest triangle inscribed in a semicircle is a right triangle\n  \
  # with its base equal to the diameter of the semicircle and its height \
equal to the radius.\n    \n    # Base of the triangle (diameter of the \
semicircle)\n    base = 2 * radius\n    # Height of the triangle (radius of \
the semicircle)\n    height = radius\n    \n    # Area of the triangle = 0.5 \
* base * height\n    area = 0.5 * base * height\n    return area\n\n# Example \
usage:\nradius = 5\narea = largest_triangle_area(radius)\nprint(f\"The area \
of the largest triangle inscribed in the semicircle with radius {radius} is \
{area}.\")\n```\n\n### Final Answer\nThe function \
`largest_triangle_area(radius)` calculates the area of the largest triangle \
inscribed in a semicircle of the given `radius`.You can use the `defaultdict` \
