first_repeated_character(s):\n    seen = set()\n    for char in s:\n        \
if char in seen:\n            return char\n        seen.add(char)\n    return \
None  # Return None if no repeated character is found\n\n# Example usage:\n\
result = first_repeated_character(\"abca\")\nprint(result)  # Output: 'a'\n\
```\n\nThis function uses a set to keep track of the characters that have \
