function that multiplies consecutive numbers in a given list:\n\n```python\n\
def multiply_consecutive(numbers):\n    if len(numbers) < 2:\n        return \
numbers  # Return the list as is if it has less than 2 elements\n    \n    \
result = []\n    for i in range(len(numbers) - 1):\n        product = \
