  return result\n\n# Example usage:\nmatrix = (\n    (1, 2, 3),\n    (4, 5, \
6),\n    (1, 2, 3),  # similar row\n    (7, 8, 9),\n    (4, 5, 6)   # similar \
row\n)\n\nunique_matrix = remove_similar_rows(matrix)\nprint(unique_matrix)\n\
```\n\n### Final Answer\nThe function `remove_similar_rows(matrix)` removes \
similar rows from a given tuple matrix and returns a list of unique rows.Here \
