values to the set\n    return list(unique_values)  # Convert the set back to \
a list and return\n\n# Example usage:\nexample_dict = {\n    'a': [1, 2, 3],\n\
    'b': [2, 3, 4],\n    'c': 5,\n    'd': [1, 5, 6]\n}\n\nunique_values = \
