Thus, the total number of sticks of wax Loraine used to make all the animals \
is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{20}\n\\]First, we calculate the amount of salt needed:\n\n\
1. Cups of flour = 16\n2. Teaspoons of salt = 1/2 * cups of flour = 1/2 * 16 \
= 8 teaspoons\n\nNext, we convert the teaspoons of salt into cups:\n\n- There \
are 48 teaspoons in 1 cup.\n- Therefore, 8 teaspoons in cups = 8 / 48 = 1/6 \
cups.\n\nNow, we can sum up all the ingredients in cups:\n\n1. Cups of water \
= 10\n2. Cups of flour = 16\n3. Cups of salt = 1/6\n\nNow we add them \
together:\n\n\\[\n10 + 16 + \\frac{1}{6} = 26 + \\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{156}{6} \
+ \\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{157}{6}\n\\]\n\nFinally, converting \\(\\frac{157}{6}\
\\) to a mixed number:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{157}{6} = 26 \\frac{1}{6}\n\\]\n\nThus, \
the combined total number of cups of water, flour, and teaspoons of salt that \
Kimber needs to make the pizza is:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{157}{6} \\text{ cups} \
\\text{ or } 26 \\frac{1}{6} \\text{ cups}\n\\]Let's denote the number of \
