\n\\[ \n290 \\text{ liters} - 80 \\text{ liters} = 210 \\text{ liters} \n\\]\n\
\nNow, determine how many cans remain. Since there are 24 cans in total and \
10 are already accounted for:\n\n\\[ \n24 \\text{ cans} - 10 \\text{ cans} = \
14 \\text{ cans} \n\\]\n\nFinally, divide the total oil in the remaining cans \
by the number of remaining cans to find out how much oil is in each of these \
cans:\n\n\\[ \n\\frac{210 \\text{ liters}}{14 \\text{ cans}} = 15 \\text{ \
liters/can} \n\\]\n\nThus, each of the remaining cans is holding **15 \
liters**.To find out how many people the boat can transport in 2 days, follow \
