\nThus, the total cost of their breakfast is **\[Sterling]15**.Let's denote \
the size of the first ball as \\( x \\). According to the problem:\n\n1. The \
second ball is twice the size of the first ball, so its size is \\( 2x \\).\n\
2. The third ball is three times the size of the first ball, so its size is \
\\( 3x \\).\n\nWe know that the amount of yarn used for the third ball is 27 \
feet. This gives us the equation:\n\n\\[\n3x = 27\n\\]\n\nTo find \\( x \\), \
we divide both sides by 3:\n\n\\[\nx = \\frac{27}{3} = 9\n\\]\n\nNow we can \
determine the size of the second ball:\n\n\\[\n2x = 2 \\times 9 = 18\n\\]\n\n\
Thus, the amount of yarn used for the second ball is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Yarn for \
the second ball} = 18 \\text{ feet}\n\\]\n\nFinal answer: **18 feet**Let's \
