2 = 10 hours\n\n3. Calculate his hourly rate with the bonus:\n   - Hourly \
rate = Total earnings / Total hours worked\n   - Hourly rate = $100 / 10 \
hours = $10 per hour\n\nTherefore, if John decides to earn the bonus, he \
makes **$10 per hour**.To find out how many crayons Mary has left after \
