equation:\n\n\\[\n7x = 847\n\\]\n\nTo find \\( x \\), we divide both sides by \
7:\n\n\\[\nx = \\frac{847}{7} = 121\n\\]\n\nThus, the number of people on the \
ship the monster ate in the first hundred years was \n\n\\[\n\\boxed{121}\n\
\\]To calculate the total download time for the 90 megabyte file, we will \
break it down into two parts based on the download rate.\n\n1. **First part \
(first 60 megabytes)**:\n   - Download rate: 5 megabytes per second\n   - \
Time to download 60 megabytes = 60 MB / 5 MB/s = 12 seconds\n\n2. **Second \
part (remaining 30 megabytes)**:\n   - Download rate: 10 megabytes per second\
\n   - Time to download 30 megabytes = 30 MB / 10 MB/s = 3 seconds\n\n3. \
**Total time**:\n   - Total time = time for first part + time for second part\
\n   - Total time = 12 seconds + 3 seconds = 15 seconds\n\nThus, the total \
time to download the file entirely is **15 seconds**.To find the number of \
goldfish below the surface, we first determine how many goldfish are at the \
surface.\n\n1. Calculate the number of goldfish at the surface:\n   \\[\n   \
\\text{Goldfish at surface} = 25\\% \\text{ of total goldfish} = 0.25 \\times \
15 = 3.75\n   \\]\n\nSince the number of goldfish must be a whole number, we \
round 3.75 to the nearest whole number, which is 4.\n\n2. Calculate the \
number of goldfish below the surface:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Goldfish below \
surface} = \\text{Total goldfish} - \\text{Goldfish at surface} = 15 - 4 = 11\
\n   \\]\n\nTherefore, the number of goldfish below the surface is \\( \
\\boxed{11} \\).To find out how many chores Gerald needs to do each month to \
save up for his baseball supplies, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. \
**Calculate Total Baseball Supply Cost**:  \n   Gerald spends $100 per month \
for 4 months.  \n   Total cost = $100 * 4 = $400.\n\n2. **Calculate Monthly \
Savings Requirement**:  \n   He needs to save $400 over the 8 months when he \
is not playing baseball (4 months of baseball + 4 months off = 8 months).  \n \
  Monthly savings = Total cost / 8 months = $400 / 8 = $50 per month.\n\n3. \
**Determine Chores Needed per Month**:  \n   Gerald charges $10 for each \
chore. To find out how many chores he needs to do to make $50:  \n   Number \
of chores = Monthly savings / Charge per chore = $50 / $10 = 5 chores.\n\n\
Thus, Gerald needs to average **5 chores per month** to save up for his \
baseball supplies.Each personal pan pizza is cut into 4 pieces. \n\n1. \
