= 2 \\) pieces\n   - Ann eats 75% of her pizza: \\( 0.75 \\times 4 = 3 \\) \
pieces\n   - Cate eats 75% of her pizza: \\( 0.75 \\times 4 = 3 \\) pieces\n\n\
3. **Calculate the total number of pieces eaten:**\n   - Total eaten = Bill's \
pieces + Dale's pieces + Ann's pieces + Cate's pieces\n   - Total eaten = \\( \
2 + 2 + 3 + 3 = 10 \\) pieces\n\n4. **Calculate the total number of pieces \
available:**\n   - Total pieces = 4 pizzas \[Times] 4 pieces/pizza = 16 \
pieces\n\n5. **Calculate the number of uneaten pieces:**\n   - Uneaten pieces \
= Total pieces - Total eaten\n   - Uneaten pieces = \\( 16 - 10 = 6 \\) \
pieces\n\nTherefore, the number of pizza pieces left uneaten is **6 \
