age will be half of Ernesto's age:\n\n\\[\nJ + 3 = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 14\n\
\\]\n\nCalculating the right side:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{1}{2} \\times 14 = 7\n\\]\n\
\nNow, we have the equation:\n\n\\[\nJ + 3 = 7\n\\]\n\nTo find Jayden's \
