last name length} = 8 + 2 = 10 \\)\n\nNow we know Bobbie's last name has 10 \
letters.\n\n3. Samantha's last name has three fewer letters than Bobbie's:\n  \
 - \\( \\text{Samantha's last name length} = 10 - 3 = 7 \\)\n\nThus, the \
number of letters in Samantha's last name is **7**.Let \\( C \\) represent \
the number of digits Carlos memorized. According to the problem:\n\n1. Mina \
memorized 6 times as many digits as Carlos:  \n   \\[\n   M = 6C\n   \\]\n   \
\n2. We know Mina memorized 24 digits of pi:  \n   \\[\n   M = 24\n   \\]\n\n\
From the second equation, we can solve for \\( C \\):\n\\[\n6C = 24\n\\]\n\
Dividing both sides by 6:\n\\[\nC = 4\n\\]\n\nNow, Sam memorized six more \
digits than Carlos:\n\\[\nS = C + 6\n\\]\nSubstituting \\( C = 4 \\):\n\\[\nS \
= 4 + 6 = 10\n\\]\n\nThus, the number of digits Sam memorized is \\( \
\\boxed{10} \\).To find out how much more Caleb spent on ice cream than on \
frozen yoghurt, we can calculate the total cost for each type of product.\n\n\
1. **Calculate the cost of ice cream:**\n   - Cost per carton of ice cream = \
