sixth term (21) is the sum of the first 6 numbers: \\\\(1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 \
= 21\\\\).\\n\\nThe nth triangular number can be calculated using the \
formula: \\n\\\\[\\nT_n = \\\\frac{n(n + 1)}{2}\\n\\\\]\\n\\nThus, the \
