      return False  # Found a non-increasing pair\\n\\n    return True  # All \
elements are in increasing order\\n\\n# Example usage\\nnumbers = [1, 2, 3, \
4, 5]\\nprint(has_increasing_trend(numbers))  # Output: True\\n\\nnumbers = \
[1, 3, 2, 4]\\nprint(has_increasing_trend(numbers))  # Output: False\\n```\\n\
