             "You can use a regular expression in Python to match a word that \
contains the letter 'z', ensuring that 'z' is not at the start or end of the \
word. Here's a function that does this:\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef \
match_word_with_z(word):\n    # Regular expression to match a word containing \
'z' not at the start or end\n    pattern = r'^[^z].*z.*[^z]$'\n    return \
bool(re.match(pattern, word))\n\n# Example usage:\n\
print(match_word_with_z(\"crazy\"))  # True\n\
print(match_word_with_z(\"zebra\"))  # False\n\
print(match_word_with_z(\"buzz\"))   # True\n\
print(match_word_with_z(\"pizza\"))  # True\nprint(match_word_with_z(\"z\"))  \
    # False\n```\n\n### Final Answer:\nThe function `match_word_with_z(word)` \
