              "\"Here is a Python function that checks whether a sequence of \
numbers has a decreasing trend:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
has_decreasing_trend(sequence):\\n    if len(sequence) < 2:\\n        return \
False  # Not enough elements to determine a trend\\n    return \
all(sequence[i] > sequence[i + 1] for i in range(len(sequence) - 1))\\n\\n# \
Example usage:\\nsequence = [5, 3, 2, \
1]\\nprint(has_decreasing_trend(sequence))  # Output: True\\n\\nsequence = \
[5, 4, 5, 3]\\nprint(has_decreasing_trend(sequence))  # Output: \
False\\n```\\n\\nThis function returns `True` if the sequence is strictly \
decreasing, and `False` otherwise.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
