lucid number <= n\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n1. **is_lucid(num)**: This \
helper function checks if a number has all unique digits by comparing the \
length of the string representation of the number with the length of the set \
of its digits.\\n2. **get_lucid_number(n)**: This function iterates from \
\\\\( n \\\\) down to 0, checking each number to see if it is lucid. It \
returns the first lucid number it finds.\\n\\nYou can call \
