list:\\n\\n```python\\ndef exchange_nth_with_n_plus_1(lst):\\n    # Iterate \
through the list with a step of 2\\n    for i in range(0, len(lst) - 1, \
2):\\n        # Swap elements at index i and i+1\\n        lst[i], lst[i + 1] \
= lst[i + 1], lst[i]\\n    return lst\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nexample_list = \
[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]\\nresult = \
exchange_nth_with_n_plus_1(example_list)\\nprint(result)  # Output: [2, 1, 4, \
3, 6, 5]\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- The function takes a list `lst` as \
input.\\n- It iterates through the list with a step of 2, swapping each \
element at index `i` with the element at index `i + 1`.\\n- The list is \
modified in place and returned after the swaps are complete.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
