cube of size n."}, {
             Style["Response:", Bold], 
             "To count the number of cubes of size \\( k \\) in a cube of \
size \\( n \\), you can use the following Python function:\n\n```python\ndef \
count_cubes(n, k):\n    if k > n:\n        return 0\n    # Calculate the \
number of positions a k-sized cube can fit in an n-sized cube\n    return (n \
- k + 1) ** 3\n\n# Example usage:\nn = 5  # size of the larger cube\nk = 2  # \
size of the smaller cube\nresult = count_cubes(n, k)\nprint(f\"Number of \
{k}x{k}x{k} cubes in a {n}x{n}x{n} cube: {result}\")\n```\n\n### Explanation:\
\n1. The function checks if \\( k \\) is greater than \\( n \\). If it is, \
you cannot fit the smaller cube in the larger one, so it returns 0.\n2. If \
\\( k \\) is less than or equal to \\( n \\), the number of cubes of size \\( \
k \\) that can fit in the cube of size \\( n \\) is given by \\( (n - k + \
1)^3 \\), which represents the number of positions along each dimension \
(length, width, height) that a cube of size \\( k \\) can occupy."}}, 
