of a given number:\n\n```python\ndef smallest_prime_divisor(n):\n    if n <= \
1:\n        return None  # No prime divisor for numbers <= 1\n    if n % 2 == \
0:\n        return 2  # 2 is the smallest prime number\n    \n    for i in \
range(3, int(n**0.5) + 1, 2):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            return i  \
# Found the smallest prime divisor\n    \n    return n  # If no divisor \
