              "\"Here is a Python function that multiplies two lists using \
the `map` function along with a `lambda` function:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
multiply_lists(list1, list2):\\n    return list(map(lambda x, y: x * y, \
list1, list2))\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nlist1 = [1, 2, 3]\\nlist2 = [4, 5, \
